  "body": "What resources do new state entries use when syncing? is it CPU bound? Network bound? Memory bound? etc\r\n\r\nI would like it to be possible to process them faster but there seems to be a limit and all my system resources are not being used for this.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.12`\r\nOS & Version: Windows\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nA flag or default behavior to use more system resources, or make new network connections, in order to pull and process chain states faster\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nA limitation with only 10% of an 8-core CPU used and not heavily. 32gb RAM.\r\n\r\nI am mainly curious about the information\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\ngeth -syncmode fast --cache 8192\r\n",
